0-07-01T06:07:42Z", "message": "Add docs for variable scopes"}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestReview", "id": "MDE3OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3NDQwNTc4NzM4", "url": "https://github.com/vividus-framework/vividus/pull/710#pullrequestreview-440578738", "createdAt": "2020-07-01T06:29:24Z", "commit": {"oid": "ffc9fa7107fa9e3f2a295434e4e154fb702455fc"}, "state": "APPROVED", "comments": {"totalCount": 2, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wNy0wMVQwNjoyOToyNFrOGrYdFg==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wNy0wMVQwNjozMjowN1rOGrYhMg==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ0ODE0MjYxNA==", "bodyText": "https://asciidoctor.org/docs/user-manual/#style\nTake a look at TIP, NOTE etc", "url": "https://github.com/vividus-framework/vividus/pull/710#discussion_r448142614", "createdAt": "2020-07-01T06:29:24Z", "author": {"login": "ikalinin1"}, "path": "docs/modules/parameters/pages/variable-scope.adoc", "diffHunk": "@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+= Variable scope\n+\n+== Description\n+\n+Defines lifecycle of a variable\n+\n+== Possible scopes\n+\n+[cols=\"1,5\", options=\"header\"]\n+|===\n+\n+|Name\n+|Description\n+\n+|step\n+|The scope is used within nested steps and discarded after the nested steps are executed.\n+\n+|scenario\n+|Variable declared with the scenario scope is available in the rest of scenario after it's declared. Scenario scoped variables are discarded once the scenario is completed.\n+\n+|story\n+|Variable declared with the story scope is available in the rest of story after it's declared. Story scoped variables are discarded once the story is completed.\n+\n+|next_batches\n+|Variable declared with the next_batches scope is available in next batches. Next_batches scoped variable is not available in batch it's declared within.\n+\n+|global\n+|Such variabes are declared only in `*.properties` files with `bdd.variables.global.` prefix and available in all stories. Attempt to save global scoped variable in stories leads to exception.\n+\n+|===\n+\n+== Notes", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "ffc9fa7107fa9e3f2a295434e4e154fb702455fc"}, "originalPosition": 32}, {"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ0ODE0MzY2Ng==", "bodyText": "Does it make sense to make scopes inside description bold?", "url": "https://github.com/vividus-framework/vividus/pull/710#discussion_r448143666", "createdAt": "2020-07-01T06:32:07Z", "author": {"login": "ikalinin1"}, "path": "docs/modules/parameters/pages/variable-scope.adoc", "diffHunk": "@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+= Variable scope\n+\n+== Description\n+\n+Defines lifecycle of a variable\n+\n+== Possible scopes\n+\n+[cols=\"1,5\", options=\"header\"]\n+|===\n+\n+|Name\n+|Description\n+\n+|step\n+|The scope is used within nested steps and discarded after the nested steps are executed.\n+\n+|scenario\n+|Variable declared with the scenario scope is available in the rest of scenario after it's declared. Scenario scoped variables are discarded once the scenario is completed.", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "ffc9fa7107fa9e3f2a295434e4e154fb702455fc"}, "originalPosition": 19}]}}, {"__typename": "PullRequestReview", "id": "MDE3OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3NDQwNDMzMjcz", "url": "https://github.com/vividus-framework/vividus/pull/710#pullrequestreview-440433273", "createdAt": "2020-06-30T22:37:51Z", "commit": {"oid": "80e39b7ae409f6002b65bafa97bafc80a1f4d0ab"}, "state": "CHANGES_REQUESTED", "comments": {"totalCount": 2, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wNi0zMFQyMjozNzo1MVrOGrQ1zw==", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyMC0wNi0zMFQyMjo0ODo0MVrOGrRDaQ==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"id": "MDI0OlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0UmV2aWV3Q29tbWVudDQ0ODAxNzg3MQ==", "bodyText": "lifecycle -> scope", "url": "https://github.com/vividus-framework/vividus/pull/710#discussion_r448017871", "createdAt": "2020-06-30T22:37:51Z", "author": {"login": "valfirst"}, "path": "do